title: Paris Saint-Germain FC (women) - Wikipedia
snippet: It is the women's football department of parent club Paris Saint-Germain FC. Founded in 1971, they compete in the Première Ligue, the top division of French football. Their home ground is the Campus PSG. PSG have played in the top flight since 2001, when they won the Seconde Ligue title.

title: Paris Saint-Germain FC - Wikipedia
snippet: Campus PSG will feature a stadium that will complement the club's stadium, the Parc des Princes, which will be built during the second phase of the project, after 2024. PSG's male team moved into Campus PSG on 10 July 2023.
